Because of "Problems with artifact sharing in Studio builds since 3.3 upgrade":

https://extranet.atlassian.com/jira/browse/BUILDENG-575

I've had to make a plan level variable that points to the fireball in the Nightly and WebDriver builds. I've made a variable {{fireball}} that points to:

{code}
/opt/bamboo-agent/bamboo-agent-home/xml-data/build-dir/JST-NIGHTLY-BUILD/studio-fireball/target/studio-fireball-110-SNAPSHOT.zip
{code}

And in the tasks, I've replaced the following:

{code}
"${bamboo.artifacts.path.studio-fireball}" studio-deploy manager-0.uc-1.atlassian.com /opt/bamboo-agent/studio-deploy studio-fireball-snapshot-nightly
{code}

With this:

{code}
"${bamboo.fireball}" studio-deploy manager-0.uc-1.atlassian.com /opt/bamboo-agent/studio-deploy studio-fireball-snapshot-nightly
{code}

We need to restore the settings when the Bamboo problem is fixed.

